.TH "__mdiobus_modify_changed" 9 "__mdiobus_modify_changed" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__mdiobus_modify_changed \- Unlocked version of the mdiobus_modify function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __mdiobus_modify_changed
.BI "(struct mii_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "int addr "  ","
.BI "u32 regnum "  ","
.BI "u16 mask "  ","
.BI "u16 set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
the mii_bus struct
.IP "addr" 12
the phy address
.IP "regnum" 12
register number to modify
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask of bits to clear
.IP "set" 12
bit mask of bits to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read, modify, and if any change, write the register value back to the
device. Any error returns a negative number.
.SH "NOTE"
MUST NOT be called from interrupt context.
